  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study hypothesis is that a quantitative index can be derived from Tc-99m myocardial
      perfusion scans that accurately identifies the presence of left ventricular hypertrophy and
      pulmonary hypertension. Echocardiography provides the reference standard.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
